# PostgreSQL Connection Examples

## Local PostgreSQL (Docker)
```bash
docker run --name postgres -e POSTGRES_PASSWORD=password -e POSTGRES_DB=interviewaceai -p 5432:5432 -d postgres:15
```

Then use:
```
DB_DSN=postgres://postgres:password@localhost:5432/interviewaceai
```

## Local PostgreSQL (Installed)
```
DB_DSN=postgres://postgres:password@localhost:5432/interviewaceai
```

## Cloud Options

### AWS RDS
```
DB_DSN=postgres://user:password@your-db.xyz.us-east-1.rds.amazonaws.com:5432/interviewaceai
```

### Azure Database for PostgreSQL
```
DB_DSN=postgres://user@servername:password@servername.postgres.database.azure.com:5432/interviewaceai
```

### Supabase (PostgreSQL)
```
DB_DSN=postgres://postgres:password@host.supabase.co:5432/postgres
```

## Testing Connection
```powershell
# Install psql if needed, then test:
psql "postgres://user:password@localhost:5432/interviewaceai" -c "SELECT 1"
```
